3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Mage Parad: Damn it... Are you guys the rumored mage
hunters...?!

Mage Parad: I, as a mere mage, have no intention of easily
giving up my life!

Clea: We'll be your opponents! Everyone, please prepare for
battle!

Black Hooded Man: 'Gather the magicians... well, as long as
there are plenty of materials, there shouldn't be a
problem.'
Black Hooded Man: First, restrain everyone.

Black Hooded Man: All five of them... It's going to be quite
a task to carry them out.
Mage Parad: Thank goodness... Who are you all?

Mage Parad: I see, so Dokuza... He may be a strange friend,
but he still has a sharp intuition.

Clea: Who could they have been? Judging from their combat
skills, they don't seem like ordinary bandits.

Mage Parad: I don't know either... But they might be a group
with a three-legged hawk emblem.

Mage Parad: I've heard rumors that there is an organization
operating in the shadows of the empire, although it's just
speculation.

Mage Parad: It is an organization called the Demon
Exorcists, who betrayed the demons and allied with the
goddesses, led by the demon Ishekeru.
Mage Relm: Why did they target Mr. Parad?

Mage Parad: I don't know either, but there are rumors that
mages are being attacked.

Mage Parad: I don't know the reason... but it might be a
good idea to warn the academy as well.
Bandit Nora: Is it safe to let him go back alone...?

Mage Relm: If he says so himself, there's no helping it. But
more importantly, you'll have to accompany me for my next
objective!

Mage Relm: Alright, let's go! This step will bring me closer
to my dream!
Bandit Nora: Didn't he just tell us to be careful~!

Clea: Sophia-san, are you okay? I feel like something has
been off with you since the battle.

Priestess Sophia: Hehe, thank you for worrying about me,
Dokusa-san. I'm surprised that your thoughts have hit the
mark.

Priestess Sophia: Now, let's go after Relm-chan and the
others, shall we?
